2. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes and evaluates methods for detecting and mitigating attacks on GNSS-based positioning, which involves system design and control. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the use of GNSS for location-aware services, which is relevant to networking and internet architecture. 
4. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper discusses the use of knowledge-based mechanisms for detecting attacks on GNSS-based positioning, which involves information theory. 
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper may involve software engineering aspects related to implementing the proposed countermeasures.
